This slide introduces the ChatGPT API and highlights two important concepts: Large Language Model (LLM) and Pre-trained.

What is ChatGPT API?

The ChatGPT API allows developers to integrate ChatGPT's capabilities into their own applications, websites, chatbots, or software. Instead of building an AI model from scratch, developers send a request to the ChatGPT API and receive an AI-generated response.

Flow:

Your Application
       │
       ▼
   ChatGPT API
       │
       ▼
Large Language Model (GPT)
       │
       ▼
AI Response
1. Large Language Model (LLM)

A Large Language Model (LLM) is an AI model trained on massive amounts of text data from books, articles, websites, and other publicly available sources.

Why is it called "Large"?
Trained on billions or trillions of words
Contains billions of parameters
Understands context, grammar, and language patterns
Can perform many language tasks
What can an LLM do?
Answer questions
Translate languages
Summarize documents
Write emails
Generate code
Create stories
Solve programming problems
Explain concepts

Example

Input:

Translate:
"I love India."

Output:

"मुझे भारत से प्यार है।"

The model understands the sentence and generates the appropriate translation.

2. Pre-trained

Pre-trained means the model has already learned language patterns before you use it.

During training, it reads enormous amounts of text and learns:

Vocabulary
Grammar
Sentence structure
Relationships between words
General knowledge
Reasoning patterns

Because of this pre-training, you don't need to teach it basic English every time you use it.

Example

When you ask:

"Write a leave letter."

The model already knows:

Letter format
Formal language
Greetings
Closing statements

It generates the response immediately because it was pre-trained on similar text.

Real-Life Analogy

Imagine hiring an experienced English teacher.

A pre-trained teacher already knows grammar and vocabulary.
You simply ask a question, and the teacher answers.

Similarly, ChatGPT is already trained, so you only provide a prompt, and it generates a response.

